**One more check**: If a job fails and is retried, will it be picked up again?
Yes, `fail` sets status to `pending` if `retries < max_retries`.
In `main.py`, `max_retries=2`. `bad_task_1` and `bad_task_2` will fail, be set to `pending` 2 times, then finally `failed`. 
Total attempts = 1 (initial) + 2 (retries) = 3.
Since the worker `process_job` loop only terminates when `dequeue` returns `None`, and `dequeue` returns `None` only when no jobs are `pending`, the loop will continue until all retries are exhausted.
Current `main.py` implementation:
`workers = [process_job(queue, i) for i in range(5)]`
`await asyncio.gather(*workers)`
This will wait until all 5 workers stop.
A worker stops when `dequeue() -> None`.
`dequeue() -> None` happens when `all(job["status"] != "pending")`.
This is correct.

